translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「はあ……あれだけご馳走が並んでいて、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Haa... With all those delicacies laid out,
and for us, just this much..."
"Well then, we will take a break from now."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「二時間後、またここに来ますので、
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "We will come here again in two hours,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: それまで仮眠を取ってもらっても構いません」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: so you can take a nap until then if you want."
"Oh? The head maid is..."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「私は城内の見回りを続けます。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "I will continue patrolling inside the castle.
Well then, see you later."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「……あの人はいつ休憩を取っているんだろう」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "...I wonder when that person takes a break."
"She's amazing, isn't she..."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「そば啜ったらとっとと寝よっと……」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Once I slurp this soba, I'll quickly go to sleep..."
Late at night, 5 o'clock—
The throne room—

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: カフェ達がこそこそと未だに起きていた。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Cafe and the others were still quietly awake.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「あら？　兵士の皆さんはみんな寝ちゃった？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Oh? Have all the soldiers fallen asleep?"
"It seems that way."
Truly a scene of many fallen.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 宴会を楽しんでいた面々はそのほとんどが
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Almost all the people who had been enjoying the banquet

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: その場に眠り込んでいた。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: were asleep right there.
At the edge of the room,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 眠っている兵士一人一人に
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: to each sleeping soldier,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 毛布を掛けるビスケッタの姿があった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: there was Viscetta putting blankets on them.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「あちゃー、ついつい話し込んじゃった。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Oh dear, I got carried away talking.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: もう起きていようかしら」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Maybe I should just stay awake now."
"Oh dear, when you get older,

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 思い出話に花が咲いちゃって」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: you end up getting lost in reminiscing stories."
"Right.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 私もすっかりお婆ちゃんなのねー」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: I've completely become an old lady too."
"Oh no, you're still young, young."
"Oh, thank you♪"
"Good morning."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「昨日からずっと飲んでたのー？」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Have you been drinking all day since yesterday?"
"Yeah.
Hehe, adults sometimes

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 夜通し飲みたい時もあるのよー」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: want to drink all night long."

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 「あれま、もう誰かしらが起きてくる時間かい。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: "Oh my, is it already time for someone to wake up?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: 小っちゃい子達の方が早起きねー」
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: The little kids sure are early risers."
"What are you eating?"
"Oh, are you hungry?

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: お鍋の残りあるから良ければ食べてー。
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: There are leftovers from the hot pot, so if you want, have some.
I'll serve it to you now."
"You seem like a granny."
"How rude."
"Hey, is this alcohol?"
"Yes, it is.
Want to try some?
Just a little, just a little."
"Hey, hey, hey.

translationLines.originalJapaneseLine: お爺さん、なにしてるの
translationLines.translatedEnglishLine: Old man, what are you doing?"
